| Paramilitary Personnel        | 4,748                     | 15,000                    | Azerbaijan has 3 times more      |

*Source: Compiled from military data ([Statista](https://www.statista.com/statistics/))*

Azerbaijan's military superiority is largely attributed to its oil-funded defense budget, enabling significant arms purchases, including drones and missile technology, primarily from Turkey and Israel. Armenia, while militarily smaller, benefits from Russian arms supplies and maintains advanced air defense systems such as the S-300 ([Edsel.G, 2014](https://www.statista.com/statistics/)).

### Economic Disparities

Azerbaijan's oil wealth has allowed it to invest heavily in military capabilities, whereas Armenia's economy is smaller and more dependent on Russia. This economic imbalance has emboldened Azerbaijan to attempt military solutions to regain control over Nagorno-Karabakh and adjacent territories ([BBC News, 2020](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-54324772)).

